## 1. Span Structure

### Span Name
`{gen_ai.operation.name} {gen_ai.request.model}` (e.g. `chat gpt-4o-mini`, `embeddings text-embedding-3-small`).

### Span Kind
Always `SpanKind.CLIENT`.

### Span Creation Attributes (set at creation time for sampling)
These 5 attributes MUST be set at `tracer.startSpan()` time via the `attributes` option:

```typescript
{
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_OPERATION]: operationName,      // "chat", "embeddings", etc.
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_PROVIDER_NAME_OTEL]: aiSystem,  // "openai", "anthropic", etc.
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_REQUEST_MODEL]: requestModel,
  [SemanticConvention.SERVER_ADDRESS]: serverAddress,
  [SemanticConvention.SERVER_PORT]: serverPort,
}
```

### Context Propagation
Wrap the original method call inside `context.with(trace.setSpan(context.active(), span), ...)` so child spans (HTTP, undici) are properly parented.

---

## 2. Span Attributes (complete list, in order)

### 2a. Required (OTel)
| Attribute | Value | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| `gen_ai.operation.name` | `"chat"`, `"embeddings"`, `"text_completion"` | Set at span creation |
| `gen_ai.provider.name` | `"openai"`, `"anthropic"`, `"cohere"`, etc. | Set at span creation |

### 2b. Conditionally Required (OTel)
| Attribute | Condition | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| `error.type` | Only on error | `e.constructor.name \|\| '_OTHER'` |
| `gen_ai.request.model` | If available | Set at span creation |
| `gen_ai.request.seed` | Only if request includes a seed (`seed != null`) | Type: `int`. Do NOT default to 0 |
| `gen_ai.request.choice.count` | Only if `n != 1` | |
| `gen_ai.output.type` | If response format is known | `"text"` or `"json"` |
| `server.address` / `server.port` | If available | Set at span creation |

### 2c. Recommended (OTel)
| Attribute | Condition | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| `gen_ai.request.temperature` | Always | Default 1 if not set |
| `gen_ai.request.top_p` | Always | Default 1 if not set |
| `gen_ai.request.max_tokens` | Only if explicitly set (`!= null`) | Do NOT use -1 sentinel |
| `gen_ai.request.frequency_penalty` | Only if non-zero | Do NOT include when 0 |
| `gen_ai.request.presence_penalty` | Only if non-zero | Do NOT include when 0 |
| `gen_ai.request.stop_sequences` | Only if set | Array of strings |
| `gen_ai.request.is_stream` | Always | `true`/`false` |
| `gen_ai.response.id` | After response | |
| `gen_ai.response.model` | After response | |
| `gen_ai.response.finish_reasons` | After response | Array: `["stop"]` |
| `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` | After response | |
| `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens` | After response | |

### 2d. OpenLIT Extension Attributes
| Attribute | Notes |
|-----------|-------|
| `telemetry.sdk.name` | Always `"openlit"` |
| `deployment.environment` | From `OpenlitConfig.environment` |
| `service.name` | From `OpenlitConfig.applicationName` |
| `gen_ai.sdk.version` | Package version |
| `gen_ai.usage.cost` | Computed from pricing info |

### 2e. Provider-Specific Attributes (example: OpenAI)
| Attribute | Condition | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| `openai.api.type` | Always | `"chat_completions"` or `"responses"` |
| `openai.response.system_fingerprint` | If present | |
| `openai.response.service_tier` | If present | |
| `openai.request.service_tier` | Only if set and != `"auto"` | |

### 2f. Opt-In (gated by `captureMessageContent`)
| Attribute | Notes |
|-----------|-------|
| `gen_ai.input.messages` | JSON string, OTel message schema |
| `gen_ai.output.messages` | JSON string, OTel message schema |
| `gen_ai.system_instructions` | If system message present |

### Key Rule: No Sentinel Values
- Do NOT set attributes to sentinel values (`0`, `-1`, `""`, `null`).
- Only set an attribute when the user explicitly provided the value or the API returned it.

