## 3. Message Format (OTel Schema)

### Input Messages
```json
[
  {"role": "user", "parts": [{"type": "text", "content": "Hello"}]},
  {"role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "tool_call", "id": "call_abc", "name": "fn", "arguments": {}}]},
  {"role": "tool", "parts": [{"type": "tool_call_response", "id": "call_abc", "result": "..."}]}
]
```

### Output Messages
```json
[{"role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "text", "content": "Hi"}], "finish_reason": "stop"}]
```

Use `OpenLitHelper.buildInputMessages()` and `OpenLitHelper.buildOutputMessages()`.

---

## 4. Events

Events are OTel Log Records emitted via `LoggerProvider`, NOT span events.

### Event Name
`gen_ai.client.inference.operation.details`

### Emission Pattern
```typescript
OpenLitHelper.emitInferenceEvent(span, {
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_OPERATION]: 'chat',
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_REQUEST_MODEL]: requestModel,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_RESPONSE_MODEL]: responseModel,
  [SemanticConvention.SERVER_ADDRESS]: serverAddress,
  [SemanticConvention.SERVER_PORT]: serverPort,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_RESPONSE_ID]: responseId,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_RESPONSE_FINISH_REASON]: [finishReason],
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_OUTPUT_TYPE]: outputType,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_USAGE_INPUT_TOKENS]: inputTokens,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_USAGE_OUTPUT_TOKENS]: outputTokens,
  // Only when captureMessageContent:
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_INPUT_MESSAGES]: inputMessagesJson,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_OUTPUT_MESSAGES]: outputMessagesJson,
});
```

### Key Rules
- Events are emitted INDEPENDENTLY of `captureMessageContent` (the event itself is always emitted; only the message content attributes within it are gated)
- Context propagation: `emitInferenceEvent` passes `trace.setSpan(otelContext.active(), span)` to correlate the log record with its parent span

---

## 5. Error Handling

### On the Span
```typescript
OpenLitHelper.handleException(span, e);
// This sets: span.recordException(e), span.setStatus(ERROR), span.setAttribute('error.type', ...)
```

### On Metrics
```typescript
BaseWrapper.recordMetrics(span, {
  ...metricParams,
  errorType: e?.constructor?.name || '_OTHER',
});
```

### Pattern
```typescript
.catch((e: any) => {
  OpenLitHelper.handleException(span, e);
  BaseWrapper.recordMetrics(span, {
    genAIEndpoint,
    model: requestModel,
    aiSystem: ProviderWrapper.aiSystem,
    serverAddress: ProviderWrapper.serverAddress,
    serverPort: ProviderWrapper.serverPort,
    errorType: e?.constructor?.name || '_OTHER',
  });
  span.end();
  throw e;
});
```

