## 11. OTel Provider Setup (must match Python SDK)

1. Check if an existing SDK provider is already registered globally
2. If yes, reuse it
3. If no (only NoopProvider found), create a new one with OpenLIT's resource and exporters
4. Exporter selection: env var driven (`OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER`). Default: OTLP if endpoint configured, else Console
5. Each provider (Tracer, Meter, Logger) has a `*_SET` flag to prevent re-initialization

---

## 12. Streaming Pattern

1. Start span before calling the original method
2. Wrap response in async generator that yields each chunk
3. Track timestamps per chunk for TTFT/TBT calculation
4. Merge tool call deltas across chunks
5. Build aggregate `result` object from chunks
6. After iteration completes: set attributes, emit event, record metrics
7. TTFT = `(firstChunkTimestamp - startTime) / 1000` (seconds)
8. TBT = average of inter-chunk durations (seconds)

